claim.claim-text:
1. A method of fabricating a stitched write head having a sunken share pole; comprising the steps of: 
a) forming a bottom coil dielectric layer over a first half shared pole over a substrate; 
b) forming coils over said bottom coil dielectric layer; 
c) forming a front second half shared pole over said first half shared pole and forming a back second half shared pole over said first half shared pole; 
d) forming a top coil dielectric layer over said bottom coil dielectric layer, said coils and said shared pole dielectric layer; 
e) planarizing by chemical-mechanical polishing said top coil dielectric layer to make said top coil dielectric layer coplanar with said second half shared poles; 
f) forming a write gap layer over said front second half shared pole and over said top coil dielectric layer above said coils; 
g) forming a upper pole over said write gap layer; 
h) etching said write gap layer and said second half shared pole, using said upper pole as an etch mask, to remove a portion of said second half shared pole adjacent to said write gap layer thereby forming a partially trimmed pole.

2. The method of claim 1 which further includes before claim 1, step (a): 
a) forming an undercoat dielectric layer over a substrate; 
b) forming a bottom shield over said undercoat dielectric layer; 
c) forming a bottom shield dielectric layer over said bottom shield and said undercoat layer; 
d) chemical-mechanical polishing said bottom shield dielectric layer and said bottom shield to make said bottom shield dielectric layer co-planar with said bottom shield; 
e) forming a read gap dielectric and MR sensor over said bottom shield dielectric layer and said bottom shield; said read gap dielectric layer surrounding said MR sensor; 
f) forming a first half shared pole over a read gap dielectric; 
g) forming a shared pole dielectric layer over said gap dielectric layer and said first half shared pole; and 
h) planarizing by chemical-mechanical polishing said shared pole dielectric layer and said first half shared pole to make said shared pole dielectric layer and coplanar said first half shared pole.

8. A method of fabricating a stitched write head having a sunken share pole; comprising the steps of: 
a) forming an undercoat dielectric layer over a substrate; 
b) forming a bottom shield over said undercoat dielectric layer; 
c) forming a bottom shield dielectric layer over said bottom shield and said undercoat layer; 
d) chemical-mechanical polishing said bottom shield dielectric layer and said bottom shield to make said bottom shield dielectric layer co-planar with said bottom shield; 
e) forming a read gap dielectric and MR sensor over said bottom shield dielectric layer and said bottom shield; said read gap dielectric layer surrounding said MR sensor; 
f) forming a first half shared pole over said read gap dielectric; 
g) forming a shared pole dielectric layer over said gap dielectric layer and said first half shared pole; 
h) planarizing by chemical-mechanical polishing said shared pole dielectric layer and said first half shared pole to make said shared pole dielectric layer and coplanar said first half shared pole; 
i) forming a bottom coil dielectric layer over said first half shared pole; 
j) forming coils over said bottom coil dielectric layer 
k) forming a front second half shared pole over said first half shared pole and forming a back second half shared pole over a portion of said first half shared pole; 
l) forming a top coil dielectric layer over said bottom coil dielectric layer said coils and said shared pole dielectric layer; 
m) chemical-mechanical polishing said top coil dielectric layer to make said top coil dielectric layer coplanar with said second half shared poles; 
n) forming a write gap layer over said front second half shared pole and said top coil dielectric layer over said coils; 
o) forming a upper pole over said write gap layer; 
p) etching said write gap layer and said second half shared pole using said upper pole as an etch mask to remove a portion of said second half shared pole adjacent to said write gap layer thereby forming a partially trimmed pole.

14. A write head having a sunken share pole comprising 
a) a bottom coil dielectric layer over said first half shared pole over a substrate; 
b) coils over said bottom coil dielectric layer, 
c) a front second half shared pole over said first half shared pole; a back second half shared pole over a portion of over said first half shared pole; 
d) a top coil dielectric layer over said bottom coil dielectric layer, said coils and said shared pole dielectric layer; 
e) said top coil dielectric layer coplanar with said second half shared poles; 
f) a write gap layer over said front second half shared pole and said top coil dielectric layer over said coils; and 
g) an upper pole over said write gap layer.

17. A write head having a sunken share pole comprising 
a) an undercoat dielectric layer over a substrate; 
b) a bottom shield over said undercoat dielectric layer; 
c) a bottom shield dielectric layer over said bottom shield and said undercoat layer, 
d) the bottom shield dielectric layer co-planar with said bottom shield; 
e) a read gap dielectric and MR sensor over said bottom shield dielectric layer and said bottom shield; said read gap dielectric layer surrounding said MR sensor; 
f) a first half shared pole over said read gap dielectric; 
g) a shared pole dielectric layer over said gap dielectric layer; said shared pole dielectric layer coplanar with said first half shared pole; 
h) a bottom coil dielectric layer over said first half shared pole; 
i) coils over said bottom coil dielectric layer; 
j) a front second half shared pole over said first half shared pole; a back second half shared pole over a portion of over said first half shared pole; 
k) a top coil dielectric layer over said bottom coil dielectric layer, said coils and said shared pole dielectric layer; 
l) said top coil dielectric layer coplanar with said second half shared poles; 
m) a write gap layer over said front second half shared pole and said top coil dielectric layer over said coils; and 
n) an upper pole over said write gap layer.
